WEBVTT

00:02.035 --> 00:05.005
[jazz music]

00:05.038 --> 00:12.078
♪ ♪

00:19.819 --> 00:21.588
[cheers and applause]

00:21.621 --> 00:23.223
- From the Penn & Teller
Theater

00:23.256 --> 00:25.225
at the Rio Hotel in Las Vegas,

00:25.258 --> 00:26.526
here's our host,

00:26.559 --> 00:29.829
Alyson Hannigan!

00:29.863 --> 00:31.831
[cheers and applause]

00:31.865 --> 00:38.905
♪ ♪

00:40.974 --> 00:42.742
- Welcome to "Fool Us."

00:42.776 --> 00:45.278
We can't wait to show you
all the magicians

00:45.311 --> 00:46.913
we have lined up
for you tonight.

00:46.946 --> 00:48.581
So we won't wait.

00:48.615 --> 00:49.716
Ladies and gentlemen,

00:49.749 --> 00:52.252
give it up
for our Las Vegas legends,

00:52.285 --> 00:54.287
Penn and Teller!

00:54.320 --> 00:57.290
[cheers and applause]

00:57.323 --> 01:04.364
♪ ♪

01:09.369 --> 01:12.572
Penn and Teller give a slot
in their world-famous show

01:12.605 --> 01:14.841
and their coveted
"Fool Us" trophy

01:14.874 --> 01:18.211
to any magician
who successfully fools them.

01:18.244 --> 01:21.514
Let's see if our first
performer can turn the trick.

01:21.548 --> 01:23.750
[fireworks boom]

01:23.783 --> 01:24.984
- So the first time
I was on "Fool Us"

01:25.018 --> 01:26.486
was about five years ago,

01:26.519 --> 01:28.354
and Penn and Teller busted me.

01:28.388 --> 01:29.856
But they didn't
actually bust me.

01:29.889 --> 01:32.192
They busted my assistant,
who was a blowup doll.

01:32.225 --> 01:33.526
- Is that enough
of a hint for you?

01:33.560 --> 01:34.527
- You got it, you got it.

01:34.561 --> 01:35.895
- Okay.
- Thanks so much.

01:35.929 --> 01:37.764
I do get a little aggressive
with the crowd.

01:37.797 --> 01:40.366
One of the biggest questions
I get asked after my shows:

01:40.400 --> 01:42.635
does anyone ever get
pissed off and want to fight?

01:42.669 --> 01:43.903
So I can see
where they're coming from.

01:43.937 --> 01:45.071
But everyone has a good time,

01:45.105 --> 01:46.272
and it's all in fun.

01:46.306 --> 01:48.308
My nightly show in Vegas
is going great,

01:48.341 --> 01:49.542
and people still come up to me

01:49.576 --> 01:51.377
saying, "We remember you
from 'Fool Us.'"

01:51.411 --> 01:53.113
This is what an average night
looks like for us.

01:53.146 --> 01:54.414
[record scratches]

01:54.447 --> 01:56.182
And tonight,
nobody's gonna forget me.

01:56.216 --> 01:57.584
Especially my victim--

01:57.617 --> 01:59.486
[clears throat]
My volunteer.

01:59.519 --> 02:02.055
Penn and Teller, tonight,
we're gonna even the score.

02:02.088 --> 02:03.256
[growls]

02:03.289 --> 02:04.424
[laughs]

02:04.457 --> 02:07.627
[cheers and applause]

02:07.660 --> 02:11.231
- Give it up for the hilarious
Mike Hammer.

02:11.264 --> 02:13.833
- All right!

02:13.867 --> 02:15.568
Thank you guys so much.
Thank you.

02:15.602 --> 02:16.903
Thanks for having me back,
guys.

02:16.936 --> 02:18.571
I was here five years ago.

02:18.605 --> 02:20.807
I usually select someone
from the audience,

02:20.840 --> 02:22.375
but tonight, you guys are safe

02:22.408 --> 02:24.477
because we've got
a special guest.

02:24.511 --> 02:26.079
He's a very funny comedian.

02:26.112 --> 02:28.114
You saw him on
"Whose Line Is It Anyway?"

02:28.148 --> 02:30.717
He's here because Drew Carey
turned me down.

02:30.750 --> 02:33.019
Ladies and gentlemen,
Brad Sherwood!

02:33.052 --> 02:34.754
Let's welcome Brad Sherwood!

02:34.787 --> 02:36.623
King of improv!

02:36.656 --> 02:37.857
I'm just messing.

02:37.891 --> 02:39.125
[cheers and applause]

02:39.159 --> 02:40.760
How are you?
- How you doing?

02:40.793 --> 02:42.028
Hello.

02:42.061 --> 02:43.463
- I didn't know
you were so big.

02:43.496 --> 02:44.831
I wouldn't have thrown
that Drew Carey comment there.

02:44.864 --> 02:45.932
- That's all right.

02:45.965 --> 02:47.300
- I just want
the audience to know

02:47.333 --> 02:48.568
we did not set this up.

02:48.601 --> 02:49.669
You do not know
what's gonna happen.

02:49.702 --> 02:50.803
- Not at all.

02:50.837 --> 02:51.804
- I barely know
what's gonna happen,

02:51.838 --> 02:53.173
so let's try this out.

02:53.206 --> 02:54.574
You got a--we need a 20.

02:54.607 --> 02:56.242
Have you got a 20 on you?

02:56.276 --> 02:58.378
- Really?
- 20--sure.

02:58.411 --> 03:00.113
- I'm already losing money
in Vegas.

03:00.146 --> 03:01.481
All right.
- Oh, yeah.

03:01.514 --> 03:02.949
Here, I'll help you out there.
- Oh, great, get it.

03:02.982 --> 03:03.950
- Okay.
[laughs]

03:03.983 --> 03:05.552
$2 bill?
Who has that?

03:05.585 --> 03:08.054
You. All right. 100!

03:08.087 --> 03:10.089
Ladies and gentlemen, we will
be using a hundred-dollar bill.

03:10.123 --> 03:11.090
Is that okay with you?
Hundred?

03:11.124 --> 03:12.392
- Well, all right--
- Yes!

03:12.425 --> 03:13.393
All right.
You heard it.

03:13.426 --> 03:16.296
Remember
the hundred-dollar bill.

03:16.329 --> 03:17.564
- Would--would you like
the money clip,

03:17.597 --> 03:18.598
as well, since you...

03:18.631 --> 03:19.632
- You don't need that.
- Okay.

03:19.666 --> 03:20.800
- Here, have a seat.
You paid for it.

03:20.833 --> 03:22.468
- Oh, terrific, all right.
[laughter]

03:22.502 --> 03:24.704
[grunts]

03:24.737 --> 03:26.039
- Close your legs, sir.
- All right.

03:26.072 --> 03:27.373
- We don't need to knock out
the front row, okay?

03:27.407 --> 03:28.975
- Try not to.

03:29.008 --> 03:30.210
- Here's what
I'd like you to do.

03:30.243 --> 03:32.378
I want you to think of a name.
Any name at all.

03:32.412 --> 03:33.947
Do not say it out loud.

03:33.980 --> 03:35.348
And you're gonna write
that name down

03:35.381 --> 03:37.217
as big as you can
on the front of the hundred.

03:37.250 --> 03:38.418
- All right.
- I'll turn away.

03:38.451 --> 03:39.986
We did not set this up.

03:40.019 --> 03:41.921
Fold it in half, Brad,
so nobody sees it.

03:41.955 --> 03:43.022
Are you doing that?

03:43.056 --> 03:44.457
- I am doing that.
- Okay.

03:44.490 --> 03:45.458
Uh, I'll take a look now.

03:45.491 --> 03:46.626
And we're good?
All right.

03:46.659 --> 03:47.727
I'm gonna take the bill
back from you.

03:47.760 --> 03:48.761
I'll fold it in half again.
- Mm-hmm.

03:48.795 --> 03:50.363
- Finely into small quarters.

03:50.396 --> 03:51.397
Oh, thank you very much.
Oh, look.

03:51.431 --> 03:53.132
Like a professional.
Fantastic.

03:53.166 --> 03:55.735
Now, you cannot see
through this bill.

03:55.768 --> 03:57.704
- No.
- How 'bout the open eye?

03:57.737 --> 03:58.705
- No.
[laughter]

03:58.738 --> 03:59.706
- I'm gonna try and guess

03:59.739 --> 04:00.940
what the name is
on this bill.

04:00.974 --> 04:02.742
But first, I need to hide this
underneath you.

04:02.775 --> 04:03.876
And no, no, no, no.

04:03.910 --> 04:04.978
Just underneath you.
Not inside you.

04:05.011 --> 04:05.979
- Oh.
I was gonna say.

04:06.012 --> 04:07.213
- Yeah.

04:07.247 --> 04:08.281
- Then I'd--I'd have
to open my legs again.

04:08.314 --> 04:09.282
- Open your legs.
- Yeah.

04:09.315 --> 04:10.617
- Well...
[laughter]

04:10.650 --> 04:12.986
For another hundred,
I'll show you some real magic.

04:13.019 --> 04:16.055
- Okay.
[laughter]

04:16.089 --> 04:18.024
I don't wanna see
anything else disappear.

04:18.057 --> 04:19.459
- Yeah, I got you.
I got you.

04:19.492 --> 04:21.160
- Behind me, that is.
- Yeah.

04:21.194 --> 04:23.263
Lean to your right side.
Lift up your left cheek.

04:23.296 --> 04:24.764
- All right.
- That's actually your leg.

04:24.797 --> 04:25.832
Here.
Do it manually.

04:25.865 --> 04:26.866
Lift it up manually.
- All right.

04:26.899 --> 04:28.501
- There you go.
There you go.

04:28.534 --> 04:29.602
And sit back down.

04:29.636 --> 04:31.604
Get off my hand.
- All right.

04:31.638 --> 04:32.972
- Brad, here's
what's going to happen.

04:33.006 --> 04:34.340
I'm gonna look in your mouth.

04:34.374 --> 04:36.042
I'm gonna see through
to the other side of your body.

04:36.075 --> 04:38.011
This is the weirdest trick
you'll ever see.

04:38.044 --> 04:39.646
- Yeah.
- I'm gonna look in his mouth.

04:39.679 --> 04:41.080
See all the way through
to the other side.

04:41.114 --> 04:42.515
Try and read the name
off the bill you're sitting on.

04:42.548 --> 04:43.783
Okay?
- Okay.

04:43.816 --> 04:44.951
- I'm gonna ask you
to tilt your head back.

04:44.984 --> 04:46.486
This'll stay on, yes?
- Yes.

04:46.519 --> 04:47.553
- Okay.
- Hope so, yeah.

04:47.587 --> 04:48.554
[laughter]

04:48.588 --> 04:50.323
Okay.
It's glued.

04:50.356 --> 04:52.992
- You--tilt your head back.
Open wide.

04:53.026 --> 04:54.661
- Sure.
- Don't breathe out.

04:54.694 --> 04:57.063
- Let me get that flashlight.
Open wide.

04:57.096 --> 04:59.565
The name starts with a B.
Is that correct?

04:59.599 --> 05:02.969
Or--or a C?

05:03.002 --> 05:04.304
Or?

05:04.337 --> 05:05.338
All right.

05:05.371 --> 05:06.339
I gotta be honest
with you, folks.

05:06.372 --> 05:07.473
I cannot see through there.

05:07.507 --> 05:09.776
There's a blockage.
- Yeah.

05:09.809 --> 05:12.178
- You were eating some snacks,
weren't you?

05:12.211 --> 05:14.447
- I had burritos earlier.
- Burritos, yeah.

05:14.480 --> 05:16.182
And peanuts?
Peanuts--I saw peanuts.

05:16.215 --> 05:17.183
- Yeah, okay.
- All right.

05:17.216 --> 05:18.318
- Peanuts!
Yes.

05:18.351 --> 05:20.053
[laughter]

05:20.086 --> 05:21.788
- We need to remove
the peanuts

05:21.821 --> 05:23.523
before we continue.

05:23.556 --> 05:25.525
[laughter]

05:25.558 --> 05:27.960
You're lucky this wasn't you,
Teller.

05:27.994 --> 05:29.762
Ladies and gentlemen,
make some noise.

05:29.796 --> 05:31.964
You're glad you're not Brad,
everybody.

05:31.998 --> 05:33.599
'Cause this could've been you.

05:33.633 --> 05:36.469
[cheers and applause]

05:36.502 --> 05:38.905
Brad, close your legs
'cause this is gonna suck.

05:38.938 --> 05:40.239
- Oh, jeez.
- All right.

05:40.273 --> 05:41.741
[laughter]

05:41.774 --> 05:44.043
- Here's what I need you to do.
[laughing]

05:44.077 --> 05:45.511
[laughter]

05:45.545 --> 05:46.846
I almost feel bad.

05:46.879 --> 05:48.748
I know what's gonna happen.
Listen.

05:48.781 --> 05:50.583
I've gotta put this
in your mouth

05:50.616 --> 05:52.185
and suck the peanuts
out of the way.

05:52.218 --> 05:54.220
But don't worry.
I'm wearing a glove.

05:54.253 --> 05:55.521
[laughter]

05:55.555 --> 05:56.923
Good.

05:56.956 --> 05:58.224
Tilt your head back.
Open wide.

05:58.257 --> 05:59.292
How's that feel?
Pretty good?

05:59.325 --> 06:00.360
All right.
Open wide.

06:00.393 --> 06:01.761
Open wide.

06:01.794 --> 06:02.862
Move to your left.

06:02.895 --> 06:04.163
Move to--there you go!

06:04.197 --> 06:05.631
All right.

06:05.665 --> 06:07.734
Stop me when you're-
[laughing]

06:07.767 --> 06:09.035
[vacuum droning]

06:09.068 --> 06:10.536
The switch was right there,

06:10.570 --> 06:12.205
and you could've stopped it
at any point.

06:12.238 --> 06:15.074
- Oh, damn it.
[laughter]

06:15.108 --> 06:16.809
- Come back tomorrow.
We'll go in the other way.

06:16.843 --> 06:17.844
- Oh.

06:17.877 --> 06:20.046
[laughter]

06:20.079 --> 06:21.247
- All right.
We'll cut that out.

06:21.280 --> 06:22.548
Open wide, Brad.

06:22.582 --> 06:24.550
Tilt your head back.

06:24.584 --> 06:26.285
Well, your nuts are gone.

06:26.319 --> 06:28.521
[laughter]

06:28.554 --> 06:30.323
Listen, I didn't see
your hundred-dollar bill.

06:30.356 --> 06:32.992
You were sitting on it.
Can you stand up?

06:33.025 --> 06:35.762
Take a look underneath you.

06:35.795 --> 06:36.863
- Uh-oh.
- Is it gone?

06:36.896 --> 06:38.164
- It's gone.
- Hell yeah!

06:38.197 --> 06:39.899
Magic.
Thank so much, man.

06:39.932 --> 06:41.334
- All right.
[laughter]

06:41.367 --> 06:42.869
Goodnight, everybody.
- [laughs]

06:42.902 --> 06:44.137
No, don't--
- What, no?

06:44.170 --> 06:45.571
- Oh, okay.
- No, no, have a seat.

06:45.605 --> 06:46.806
Close your legs.
- Oh, all right.

06:46.839 --> 06:49.075
- I don't know if you
remember that part.

06:49.108 --> 06:52.011
You were sitting on a bill,
and then we sucked it out.

06:53.980 --> 06:56.015
Nice and loud.

06:56.048 --> 06:58.184
What's inside the vacuum?

07:00.386 --> 07:01.988
- It's my nuts.

07:02.021 --> 07:04.557
[laughter]

07:04.590 --> 07:06.859
- Take 'em out first
before you say it.

07:06.893 --> 07:08.728
Hold those up nice and high.
- Oh, it is my nuts!

07:08.761 --> 07:10.329
- Show the audience.
Show the audience.

07:10.363 --> 07:13.433
Hold them up nice and high so
the audience can see your nuts.

07:13.466 --> 07:15.601
Ladies and gentlemen,
one more thing.

07:15.635 --> 07:17.069
Look inside the vacuum.

07:17.103 --> 07:19.872
Do you see
a hundred-dollar bill?

07:19.906 --> 07:21.340
- I do not.
- No.

07:21.374 --> 07:23.476
'Cause then I would've been
Penn and Teller.

07:23.509 --> 07:25.244
[laughter]

07:25.278 --> 07:27.580
But if we push

07:27.613 --> 07:30.450
his nuts aside...

07:30.483 --> 07:32.084
there's something special
in here.

07:32.118 --> 07:34.253
It's difficult to see
if you're further back.

07:34.287 --> 07:36.889
I can tell by
the lack of response.

07:36.923 --> 07:38.858
[laughter]

07:38.891 --> 07:40.193
Brad, there's something
special in there.

07:40.226 --> 07:42.462
There's a bill in there.
Can you hold out both hands?

07:42.495 --> 07:44.430
Closer, like you're
gonna catch your nuts.

07:44.464 --> 07:46.833
[laughter]

07:46.866 --> 07:49.168
Amongst your nuts,
what do you see?

07:49.202 --> 07:51.270
"My hundred."
Good.

07:51.304 --> 07:53.105
[laughter]

07:53.139 --> 07:55.641
You're too good
for this routine.

07:55.675 --> 07:57.577
Did you write the name Snoopy?
- I did.

07:57.610 --> 07:58.978
- Is that the same bill?
- I wrote Snoopy.

07:59.011 --> 08:00.112
- There it is,
ladies and gentlemen!

08:00.146 --> 08:02.048
[cheers and applause]

08:02.081 --> 08:04.517
Same bill, same guy, same nuts.

08:04.550 --> 08:06.886
Let's give it up
for Brad, everybody.

08:06.919 --> 08:08.521
I'm gonna give you this
as a souvenir.

08:08.554 --> 08:09.922
- Thank you so much.

08:09.956 --> 08:11.891
- And here's a few bucks
for being a good sport.

08:11.924 --> 08:13.092
- Oh!
Thank you so much.

08:13.125 --> 08:14.427
- You're awesome.
Thank you so much.

08:14.460 --> 08:15.561
- My pleasure.

08:15.595 --> 08:16.929
- Keep it going on
for Brad Sherwood,

08:16.963 --> 08:17.964
ladies and gentlemen!

08:17.997 --> 08:19.499
Thank you so much, Brad.

08:19.532 --> 08:21.534
[cheers and applause]
Thank you so much.

08:21.567 --> 08:24.604
- Mike Hammer, everyone!

08:24.637 --> 08:26.839
Oh, thank you so much

08:26.873 --> 08:28.541
for not asking me to volunteer.

08:28.574 --> 08:29.742
- Well, there...

08:29.775 --> 08:31.410
[laughter]

08:31.444 --> 08:33.846
- Do you always abuse
the people you bring on stage?

08:33.880 --> 08:34.847
- Yeah.

08:34.881 --> 08:36.182
I wanted to get Penn,

08:36.215 --> 08:38.017
but they said that wouldn't
be good for my life.

08:38.050 --> 08:40.419
- [laughing]
- So...

08:40.453 --> 08:42.455
- So does it ever go wrong?

08:42.488 --> 08:43.623
- I've had some
weird things happen.

08:43.656 --> 08:45.992
I had a--I do a--a trick

08:46.025 --> 08:47.527
where I bring someone
up on stage.

08:47.560 --> 08:49.228
And I had my hands tied
behind my back.

08:49.262 --> 08:50.396
It's not an escape,

08:50.429 --> 08:52.131
but I'm gonna do
a pickpocket demonstration

08:52.164 --> 08:53.399
with my hands tied.

08:53.432 --> 08:56.602
And the guy tied me up
and then left the stage.

08:56.636 --> 08:57.637
- [laughs]

08:57.670 --> 08:59.839
- And I'm standing there
just tied up.

08:59.872 --> 09:00.907
I told the audience--I said,

09:00.940 --> 09:02.508
"Will someone come up
and untie me?"

09:02.542 --> 09:03.976
But they thought
it was part of the show.

09:04.010 --> 09:05.411
- Oh, my goodness.
- Yeah.

09:05.444 --> 09:06.679
All right.
Well, let's find out

09:06.712 --> 09:08.381
if the boys know how you
did--did your trick.

09:08.414 --> 09:09.482
- Okay.
Thank you.

09:09.515 --> 09:11.017
- Boys.

09:11.050 --> 09:12.351
- It's so--

09:12.385 --> 09:13.819
You know, Brad Sherwood's
an old friend of ours.

09:13.853 --> 09:14.887
- Yeah.

09:14.921 --> 09:16.255
- You're an old friend
of ours.

09:16.289 --> 09:18.057
We were just relaxing
and watching you work.

09:18.090 --> 09:19.759
- Oh, thanks so much, guys.
Thanks for having me back.

09:19.792 --> 09:20.927
- Great time.
- Thank you.

09:20.960 --> 09:23.162
- And I wanna point out

09:23.195 --> 09:24.997
you're at the Four Queens

09:25.031 --> 09:26.499
on Fremont Street...
- Yes.

09:26.532 --> 09:28.067
- Doing magic all the time.

09:28.100 --> 09:29.101
- Yeah.
[cheers and applause]

09:29.135 --> 09:30.970
- I believe

09:31.003 --> 09:32.605
that's the most important thing

09:32.638 --> 09:33.873
you wanted to hear
out of me, right?

09:33.906 --> 09:35.675
- [laughing]

09:35.708 --> 09:37.843
- Once I've said
you're at the Four Queens...

09:37.877 --> 09:39.011
- I can leave!
- Doing magic nightly.

09:39.045 --> 09:40.246
You'll be able to say, "Yep.

09:40.279 --> 09:41.247
They busted me.
Bye."

09:41.280 --> 09:42.315
- They busted me.
See you.

09:42.348 --> 09:44.083
No, I appreciate that.
Thank you so much.

09:44.116 --> 09:45.551
- It's wonderful
to see you again.

09:45.585 --> 09:46.552
- Oh, great to see you.

09:46.586 --> 09:47.954
- I guess I do have to get to

09:47.987 --> 09:49.055
what the show
is actually about.

09:49.088 --> 09:50.289
- No! You don't.

09:50.323 --> 09:51.490
You could just keep talking
about my show.

09:51.524 --> 09:54.260
[laughter]

09:55.995 --> 09:57.630
- But I will say,
last time you were on,

09:57.663 --> 09:59.031
we talked about
a cartoon bunny.

09:59.065 --> 10:00.333
- Yeah.

10:00.366 --> 10:02.168
- And this time, we'll talk
about another comic book.

10:02.201 --> 10:03.869
"Superman."
- Okay.

